<subSubSection id="5DE6D9C0CE98D4CA44E783448AC46743" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BA708B219B5C8DE7FDC3AB1123661150" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="611B23BCFC34558B03386F682250084C" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">
Southern Mexico to Costa Rica, and in western Cuba. A collection stated to be from St. Lucia (the type of 
<taxonomicName id="8C7A76FD4A2E370D0FD3B8EE19C27A41" authorityName="Sprague" authorityYear="1921" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Belotia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caribaea">Belotia caribaea</taxonomicName>
) represents either material cultivated in the St. Vincent Botanic Garden or mislabeled material from Cuba (
<bibRefCitation id="136986A95B2EABE8CF9E9A98FC26512C" author="Bornstein, AJ" editor="Howard, RA" journalOrPublisher="Jamaica Plain, Massachusetts: Arnold Arboretum, Harvard University" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="184 - 199" refId="B1" refString="Bornstein, AJ, 1989. Tiliaceae. In: Howard, RA, Ed., Flora of the Lesser Antilles, vol. 5. Jamaica Plain, Massachusetts: Arnold Arboretum, Harvard University: 184 - 199" title="Tiliaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of the Lesser Antilles, vol. 5." year="1989">Bornstein 1989: 185-186</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6D4CDECD4C077D2333EA2A0FFD149A4" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" type="note">
<paragraph id="CB6DAB7D060E012C098A99113C803C51" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="345CD7D17E1AE2C4649038E9D77DF73B" pageId="3" pageNumber="20">
The name 
<taxonomicName id="63DF1467D320B3EE8F10B0CAD38643E6" authorityName="Kosterm" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Trichospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="grewiifolium">Trichospermum grewiifolium</taxonomicName>
(A. Rich.) Kosterm. is frequently applied to this species, but it is illegitimate because as explained in the text 
<taxonomicName id="36E28123503043EE976CF845D960F750" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Belotia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grewiifolia">Belotia grewiifolia</taxonomicName>
A. Rich. was nomenclaturally superfluous when published (
<bibRefCitation id="408244C47DFFC5B3B50D46B48E1C28AF" author="McNeill, J" journalOrPublisher="Regnum Vegetabile 146" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 568" refId="B11" refString="McNeill, J, Barrie, FR, Burdet, HM, Demoulin, V, Hawksworth, DL, Marhold, K, Nicolson, DH, Prado, J, Silva, PC, Skog, JE, Wiersema, JH, Turland, NJ, 2006. International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress, Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Vegetabile 146 i-xviii: 1 - 568" title="International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress, Vienna, Austria, July 2005." volume="i-xviii" volumeTitle="Regnum Vegetabile 146" year="2006">McNeill et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 52.1) and cannot serve as the basionym for this combination. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="1A927567BBE7A8F10D3638A84C17EC16" author="Rodriguez Fuentes, A" editor="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Flora de la Republica de Cuba: Serie A, Plantas Vasculares" pageId="5" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 38" refId="B16" refString="Rodriguez Fuentes, A, 2000. Tiliaceae. Flora de la Republica de Cuba: Serie A, Plantas Vasculares 3 (5): 1 - 38" title="Tiliaceae." volume="3" volumeTitle="Flora de la Republica de Cuba: Serie A, Plantas Vasculares" year="2000">
<normalizedToken id="2F783275DDB52C933BC9D8BA428DE0F0" originalValue="Rodríguez">Rodriguez</normalizedToken>
Fuentes (2000: 32)
</bibRefCitation>
accepted 
<taxonomicName id="10076E205E1F1D829C5470EF53A72DE1" authorityName="Kosterm" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Trichospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="grewiifolium">Trichospermum grewiifolium</taxonomicName>
as a new species published by 
<bibRefCitation id="8660FEA906247E2148B9C22FC8848BFE" author="Kostermans, AJGH" journalOrPublisher="Reinwardtia" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="277 - 279" refId="B9" refString="Kostermans, AJGH, 1962. The genera Belotia Rich. and Trichospermum Bl. (Tiliaceae). Reinwardtia 6 (3): 277 - 279" title="The genera Belotia Rich. and Trichospermum Bl. (Tiliaceae)." volume="6" year="1962">Kostermans (1962)</bibRefCitation>
apparently in the belief that Kostermans had explicitly excluded the purported 
<normalizedToken id="EEA86207CE2386A2685142B036BB4E29" originalValue="basionym’s">basionym's</normalizedToken>
type, but this is debatable and in any case 
<taxonomicName id="CAFD22272A571F7E63D42E0910DB4A00" authorityName="Kosterm" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Trichospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="20" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="grewiifolium">Trichospermum grewiifolium</taxonomicName>
is not a valid name as Kostermans failed to designate a nomenclatural type (
<bibRefCitation id="296F29F901D3409C1ED446E36B1EBD12" author="McNeill, J" journalOrPublisher="Regnum Vegetabile 146" pageId="4" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 568" refId="B11" refString="McNeill, J, Barrie, FR, Burdet, HM, Demoulin, V, Hawksworth, DL, Marhold, K, Nicolson, DH, Prado, J, Silva, PC, Skog, JE, Wiersema, JH, Turland, NJ, 2006. International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress, Vienna, Austria, July 2005. Regnum Vegetabile 146 i-xviii: 1 - 568" title="International Code of Botanical Nomenclature (Vienna Code) adopted by the Seventeenth International Botanical Congress, Vienna, Austria, July 2005." volume="i-xviii" volumeTitle="Regnum Vegetabile 146" year="2006">McNeill et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 37.1).
</paragraph>
